snippet.textDisplay: I remember the first modern meme I ever saw. It must have been early 2010s. Before then I’d only seen vice animals  or “bad luck Brian” or Rage Comics type memes, stuff that had very solid guidelines and formats. Then one December I went away and had no internet and when I came back “They crave that mineral” was EVERYWHERE with no original source or format in sight, I was so confused but I absolutely loved seeing it everywhere. I know it’s no where close to being the first modern viral meme but it still means a lot to me.
